"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The fixed size of NumPy numeric types may cause overflow errors when a value requires more memory than available in the data type. In this case, the value of factorial(21) is too large to be represented by the default NumPy float type.\", \"patch\": \"4c4\\n< print(np.log(float(factorial(21))))\\n---\\n> print(np.log(np.longdouble(factorial(21))))\\n\"}"